README - porting uclinux on av3xx
by Oxygen

To patch the uclinux kernel, you need:
- the right kernel version (download on files section of linav.sf.net)
- the patch from cvs
- the initial rom if you want to use blkmem instead of the harddisk. This file can be found in the file section of linav.sf.net.

To apply the patch:
- untar the kernel sources
- apply the patch with zcat patch-xxxx | patch -p0 -E
where patch-xxxx is the patch you are trying to apply
- put rom.inc in arch/armnommu/mach-av3xx

To build the kernel:
make mrproper
make menuconfig (not xconfig)
	in system type:
		(Av3xx) ARM system type
		(RAM) Kernel executes from
		[*] Debug on serial low level
	in Block devices:
		[*] ROM disk memory block device (blkmem)
	in File systems
		[*] ROM file system support

make dep
make
objcopy -O binary linux linux-exe.bin 
objcopy -O binary arch/armnommu/mach-av3xx/boot.o boot.bin
(where objcopy is the one from your toolchain)
cat boot.bin linux-exe.bin > linux.bin

you can then run linux.bin from the bootloader.

	
